Major News Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers
JERUSALEM , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Israeli newspapers Sunday .
The Jerusalem Post :
-- For the first time since last month 's Wye agreement , Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat publicly revived the idea Saturday of unilaterally declaring an independent state on May 4 , 1999 , prompting an angry reaction from Israel .
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu 's adviser David Bar-Illan reiterated Israel 's position that such an act would be " not just a violation of the accord - but its cancellation . "
Haaretz :
-- Inflation figures for October will show a record consumer price index ( CPI ) rise of 3 to 4 percent , the highest monthly rise in 13 years , experts predict .
The high rate foils the efforts of economic leaders to reduce the annual inflation rate to a level of just a few percent .
